<paragraph blockId="14.[813,1420,1936,2091]" pageId="14" pageNumber="1017">Cryptophyte, native with distribution in the Southern Cone Region of South America.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[168,776,160,586]" pageId="15" pageNumber="1018">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[206,381,160,184]" pageId="15" pageNumber="1018">Characteristics.</emphasis>
Terrestrial herb, 
<quantity box="[552,653,160,184]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" metricValueMax="7.0" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="15" pageNumber="1018" unit="cm" value="55.0" valueMax="70.0" valueMin="40.0">40–70 cm</quantity>
tall, including inflorescence, with folded, fleshy roots. Basal leaves 5 or 6, elliptic in shape, to 
<quantity box="[433,498,227,251]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="15" pageNumber="1018" unit="cm" value="15.0">15 cm</quantity>
long, with subacute apex. Inflorescence: a raceme; flowers greenish-white; labellum margin entire or slightly trilobed, covered by cilindrical, capitated, darker, blackish-brown to black appendices. Stamens with anthers inclined. Fruit: a capsule.
</paragraph>
