<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="1018" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="15.[168,776,160,586]" pageId="15" pageNumber="1018">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[206,336,394,418]" pageId="15" pageNumber="1018">Comments.</emphasis>
This is a rare species in the study area. It grows in damp soils, in shady places under trees. 
<taxonomicName box="[168,428,461,485]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Chloraea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="15" pageNumber="1018" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="membranacea">
<emphasis box="[168,428,461,485]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="1018">Chloraea membranacea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the only species of 
<taxonomicName box="[674,775,461,485]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Chloraea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="15" pageNumber="1018" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[674,775,461,485]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="1018">Chloraea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
known from 
<collectingRegion box="[308,553,495,519]" country="Argentina" name="Buenos Aires" pageId="15" pageNumber="1018">Buenos Aires province</collectingRegion>
and is distinguished from other 
<taxonomicName box="[294,427,528,552]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="15" pageNumber="1018" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Orchidaceae</taxonomicName>
by its folded, thickened, fleshy roots, and its inclined anthers.
</paragraph>
